It was not the first time he took my car as a power move. He would also often take my puppy without telling me, and had a habit of “forgetting” that we had obedience classes when he would take her out to Oregon City to see his parents.

This was the first time in almost 2 years that someone else was witness to one of his tantrums. I felt crazy trying to describe them to our mutual friends because he was SO DIFFERENT around other people.
His dad came and picked him up. The only thing he packed up was his computer. I changed the locks because I didn’t want him in the house alone after he had threatened to hurt my pets.

It was actually less than 5 months. 

He lost his GD mind when our friend (who had cancelled plans with to play World of Warcraft) jokingly unplugged the wireless router. No joke- lost his fucking mind. In a fit of rage he stole my car. I called his parents.
